  "text": "The probabilistic framework requires that several model runs be included to provide a distribution of projected outcomes. In this work we weight all combinations of global model and downscaling technique equally (except for the multiple ensemble members available from a single global model using BCSD, as described below), following the approach used in the last IPCC assessment (IPCC 2007). [CITATION_1] looked specifically at the western US and concluded that weighting by model quality does not make a difference to climate projections until after the time period considered here (the 2060s).",
